a) A x B is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is in A and b is in B. Similarly, B x A is the set of all ordered pairs (b, a) where b is in B and a is in A.

A x B = {(1, 4), (1, 5), (2, 4), (2, 5), (3, 4), (3, 5)}

B x A = {(4, 1), (4, 2), (4, 3), (5, 1), (5, 2), (5, 3)}

b) The union of two sets A and B, denoted A U B, is the set of all elements that are in A, in B, or in both.

A x B U B x A = {(1, 4), (1, 5), (2, 4), (2, 5), (3, 4), (3, 5), (4, 1), (4, 2), (4, 3), (5, 1), (5, 2), (5, 3)}
